{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Repeal \"The Platform Operators Regulations 2023\"",
        "additional_details": "Online \"platforms\" are now required to verify the ID of \"sellers\" who sell any type of goods/services. The platform must report the personal details of \"sellers\" and their sales records to HMRC. Platforms can be fined \u00a35,000 + \u00a3600 per day for failing to provide information to HMRC. Platforms will now have to verify the ID of ALL sellers to avoid the heavy fines, possibly making a loss on customers who only sell a few items or passing on this cost to sellers.\r\n",
        "background": "The Platform Operators (Due Diligence and Reporting Requirements) Regulations 2023 must be repealed. I think the law unfairly and unnecessarily requires website \"platforms\" to retain and share \"seller\" and \"casual seller\" information with HMRC.",
